The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), on Monday, said it has constituted a committee to screen its aspirants for the July 16, 2022 Osun State governorship election. Hon. Umar M. Bature, National Organizing Secretary of PDP, in a statement on Monday, named members of the screening committee as; Mohammed Adoke Bello, SAN – Chairman, Amb. Sen. Aminu Wali Member; Hon. Mrs. Nnenna Ukeje – Member, H.E. Fidelis Tapgun – Member, Chief Rahman Owokoniran – South-West Zonal Secretary. According to him, the screening exercise is scheduled for Wednesday, January 12, 2022, at the NEC Hall of the PDP national secretariat, Abuja at 10 am. “All aspirants, critical stakeholders and members of our party in Osun State are by this guided accordingly,” he said